import pandas as pd
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.utils import resample

# Load your combined dataset
# If you still have separate CSVs, load them and concatenate first
df_1and2 = pd.read_csv('burns_1and2.csv')
df_3 = pd.read_csv('burns_3rd.csv')
df_1and2['binary_label'] = 0
df_3['binary_label'] = 1
df_all = pd.concat([df_1and2, df_3], ignore_index=True)

# Separate majority/minority classes
df_majority = df_all[df_all['binary_label'] == 0]  # 1st/2nd degree
df_minority = df_all[df_all['binary_label'] == 1]  # 3rd degree

# Oversample minority class
df_minority_upsampled = resample(df_minority,
                                 replace=True,
                                 n_samples=len(df_majority),
                                 random_state=42)

# Combine and shuffle
df_balanced = pd.concat([df_majority, df_minority_upsampled]) \
                 .sample(frac=1, random_state=42) \
                 .reset_index(drop=True)

# Train-validation split
train_df, val_df = train_test_split(df_balanced,
                                    test_size=0.2,
                                    stratify=df_balanced['binary_label'],
                                    random_state=42)

print("Training set distribution:\n", train_df['binary_label'].value_counts())
print("Validation set distribution:\n", val_df['binary_label'].value_counts())

print(f"Training samples: {len(train_df)} (1st/2nd: {len(train_df[train_df['binary_label']==0])}, 3rd: {len(train_df[train_df['binary_label']==1])})")
print(f"Validation samples: {len(val_df)} (1st/2nd: {len(val_df[val_df['binary_label']==0])}, 3rd: {len(val_df[val_df['binary_label']==1])})")

# GRAYSCALE TRANSFORMS - All normalization changed to single channel
import albumentations as A

# Original working model augmentation (EXACT from Document 2 - adapted for grayscale)
original_transform = A.Compose([
    A.Resize(224, 224),
    A.HorizontalFlip(p=0.5),
    A.RandomRotate90(p=0.5),
    A.RandomBrightnessContrast(brightness_limit=0.2, contrast_limit=0.2, p=0.5),
    # HueSaturationValue removed - doesn't work with grayscale
    A.GaussianBlur(blur_limit=3, p=0.3),
    A.CLAHE(clip_limit=2.0, tile_grid_size=(8, 8), p=0.3),
    A.Affine(translate_percent=0.1, scale=1.1, rotate=15, p=0.5),
    A.Normalize(mean=(0.5,), std=(0.5,))  # Single channel normalization
])

# Base augmentation (conservative)
base_transform = A.Compose([
    A.Resize(224, 224),
    A.HorizontalFlip(p=0.5),
    A.RandomRotate90(p=0.5),
    A.RandomBrightnessContrast(brightness_limit=0.15, contrast_limit=0.15, p=0.5),
    A.Normalize(mean=(0.5,), std=(0.5,))  # Single channel normalization
])

# Heavy augmentation (aggressive)
heavy_transform = A.Compose([
    A.Resize(224, 224),
    A.HorizontalFlip(p=0.5),
    A.RandomRotate90(p=0.5),
    A.RandomBrightnessContrast(brightness_limit=0.25, contrast_limit=0.25, p=0.7),
    # HueSaturationValue removed - doesn't work with grayscale
    A.GaussianBlur(blur_limit=3, p=0.4),
    A.CLAHE(clip_limit=2.0, tile_grid_size=(8, 8), p=0.4),
    A.Affine(translate_percent=0.1, scale=1.1, rotate=15, p=0.6),
    A.CoarseDropout(max_holes=8, max_height=32, max_width=32, p=0.3),
    A.Normalize(mean=(0.5,), std=(0.5,))  # Single channel normalization
])

# Medical-focused augmentation (lighting variations)
medical_transform = A.Compose([
    A.Resize(224, 224),
    A.HorizontalFlip(p=0.5),
    A.RandomBrightnessContrast(brightness_limit=0.3, contrast_limit=0.3, p=0.8),
    A.CLAHE(clip_limit=3.0, tile_grid_size=(8, 8), p=0.6),
    # HueSaturationValue removed - doesn't work with grayscale
    A.GaussNoise(var_limit=(10.0, 50.0), p=0.3),
    A.Normalize(mean=(0.5,), std=(0.5,))  # Single channel normalization
])

# Large image augmentation (256x256)
large_transform = A.Compose([
    A.Resize(256, 256),
    A.HorizontalFlip(p=0.5),
    A.RandomRotate90(p=0.5),
    A.RandomBrightnessContrast(brightness_limit=0.2, contrast_limit=0.2, p=0.6),
    A.CLAHE(clip_limit=2.0, tile_grid_size=(8, 8), p=0.4),
    A.Normalize(mean=(0.5,), std=(0.5,))  # Single channel normalization
])

# Validation transform (consistent across all models)
val_transform = A.Compose([
    A.Resize(224, 224),
    A.Normalize(mean=(0.5,), std=(0.5,))  # Single channel normalization
])

val_transform_large = A.Compose([
    A.Resize(256, 256),
    A.Normalize(mean=(0.5,), std=(0.5,))  # Single channel normalization
])

class EnsembleDataGenerator(Sequence):
    """Data generator that keeps images as GRAYSCALE for 1-channel models"""
    def __init__(self, df, batch_size=32, transform=None, shuffle=True, img_size=(224, 224), **kwargs):
        super().__init__(**kwargs)
        self.df = df.reset_index(drop=True)
        self.batch_size = batch_size
        self.transform = transform
        self.shuffle = shuffle
        self.img_size = img_size
        self.indexes = np.arange(len(self.df))
        self.on_epoch_end()
    
    def __len__(self):
        return int(np.ceil(len(self.df) / self.batch_size))
    
    def __getitem__(self, idx):
        batch_indexes = self.indexes[idx * self.batch_size:(idx + 1) * self.batch_size]
        batch_df = self.df.iloc[batch_indexes]
        
        images = []
        labels = []
        
        for _, row in batch_df.iterrows():
            img = cv2.imread(row['filepath'])
            if img is None:
                print(f"Warning: Could not load image {row['filepath']}")
                continue
            
            # CRITICAL: Convert to GRAYSCALE for 1-channel models
            if len(img.shape) == 3:
                # Convert BGR/RGB to grayscale
                img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
            
            # Ensure grayscale image has shape (H, W, 1)
            if len(img.shape) == 2:
                img = np.expand_dims(img, axis=-1)  # Add channel dimension
            
            # Resize to target size
            img = cv2.resize(img, self.img_size)
            
            # Re-add channel dimension after resize if needed
            if len(img.shape) == 2:
                img = np.expand_dims(img, axis=-1)
            
            if self.transform:
                # For albumentations with grayscale
                transformed = self.transform(image=img)
                img = transformed['image']
            else:
                img = img / 255.0
            
            images.append(img)
            labels.append(row['binary_label'])
        
        return np.array(images), np.array(labels)
    
    def on_epoch_end(self):
        if self.shuffle:
            np.random.shuffle(self.indexes)

# WORKING MODEL ARCHITECTURES 
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import layers, models
from tensorflow.keras.applications import (
    EfficientNetB0, EfficientNetB1, ResNet50, DenseNet121
)
from tensorflow.keras.metrics import Precision, Recall

def create_original_efficientnet(input_shape=(224, 224, 1), class_weights=None):
    """EXACT replica of original working EfficientNet - HARDCODED for grayscale"""
    # HARDCODE grayscale settings model
    base_model = EfficientNetB0(weights=None, include_top=False, input_shape=(224, 224, 1))
    
    # Unfreeze EXACTLY last 20 layers (same as original)
    for layer in base_model.layers[:-20]:
        layer.trainable = False
    for layer in base_model.layers[-20:]:
        layer.trainable = True
    
    # EXACT architecture from Document 2
    model = models.Sequential([
        base_model,
        layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D(),
        layers.BatchNormalization(),
        layers.Dropout(0.3),
        layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),
        layers.BatchNormalization(), 
        layers.Dropout(0.5),
        layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
    ])
    
    # EXACT compilation settings
    model.compile(
        optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
        loss='binary_crossentropy',
        metrics=['accuracy', Precision(name='precision'), Recall(name='recall')]
    )
    
    return model

def create_efficientnet_b0(input_shape=(224, 224, 1), class_weights=None):

        layer.trainable = True
    
    model = models.Sequential([

        layers.Dropout(0.3),

# ENSEMBLE TRAINING LOOP
def train_ensemble_model(model_name, create_model_fn, train_transform, val_transform, 
                        input_shape=(224, 224, 3), epochs=25):
    """Train a single model in the ensemble"""
    
    print(f"\n{'='*60}")
    print(f"TRAINING {model_name.upper()}")
    print(f"{'='*60}")
    
    # Calculate class weights
    y_train = train_df['binary_label'].values
    weights = class_weight.compute_class_weight(class_weight='balanced', 
                                               classes=np.unique(y_train), y=y_train)
    class_weights = dict(enumerate(weights))
    print(f"Class weights: {class_weights}")
    
    # Create data generators
    img_size = input_shape[:2]
    train_gen = EnsembleDataGenerator(train_df, transform=train_transform, img_size=img_size)
    val_gen = EnsembleDataGenerator(val_df, transform=val_transform, shuffle=False, img_size=img_size)
    
    # Create model
    model = create_model_fn(input_shape=input_shape, class_weights=class_weights)
    print(f"Model parameters: {model.count_params():,}")
    
    # Callbacks
    model_callbacks = [
        callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_accuracy', patience=8, restore_best_weights=True),
        callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.5, patience=5, min_lr=1e-7),
        callbacks.ModelCheckpoint(f'{model_name}_best.weights.h5', monitor='val_accuracy', 
                                 save_best_only=True, save_weights_only=True)
    ]
    
    # Train model
    history = model.fit(
        train_gen,
        validation_data=val_gen,
        epochs=epochs,
        class_weight=class_weights,
        callbacks=model_callbacks,
        verbose=1
    )
    
    # Load best weights
    model.load_weights(f'{model_name}_best.weights.h5')
    
    # Evaluate on validation set
    val_preds = model.predict(val_gen, verbose=0)
    val_labels = val_df['binary_label'].values
    
    # Calculate metrics
    val_auc = roc_auc_score(val_labels, val_preds)
    val_preds_binary = (val_preds > 0.5).astype(int).flatten()
    val_report = classification_report(val_labels, val_preds_binary, output_dict=True, zero_division=0)
    
    print(f"\n{model_name} Results:")
    print(f"AUC: {val_auc:.4f}")
    print(f"3rd degree recall: {val_report['1']['recall']:.3f}")
    print(f"3rd degree precision: {val_report['1']['precision']:.3f}")
    print(f"3rd degree F1: {val_report['1']['f1-score']:.3f}")
    print(f"Overall accuracy: {val_report['accuracy']:.3f}")
    
    # Save model
    model.save(f'{model_name}_full.h5')
    
    return {
        'model': model,
        'history': history,
        'predictions': val_preds.flatten(),
        'auc': val_auc,
        'metrics': val_report,
        'name': model_name
    }

#  ENSEMBLE COMBINATION & OPTIMIZATION

# Get all predictions
val_labels = val_df['binary_label'].values
all_predictions = {}
individual_aucs = {}

for name, result in ensemble_results.items():
    all_predictions[name] = result['predictions']
    individual_aucs[name] = result['auc']
    print(f"{name:15s}: AUC = {result['auc']:.4f}")

# Test different ensemble methods
def test_ensemble_method(predictions_dict, labels, method='simple_average'):
    """Test different ensemble combination methods"""
    
    pred_arrays = [preds for preds in predictions_dict.values()]
    
    if method == 'simple_average':
        ensemble_preds = np.mean(pred_arrays, axis=0)
    elif method == 'weighted_average':
        # Weight by individual AUC scores
        weights = np.array([individual_aucs[name] for name in predictions_dict.keys()])
        weights = weights / weights.sum()  # Normalize
        ensemble_preds = np.average(pred_arrays, axis=0, weights=weights)
    elif method == 'best_3_average':
        # Use only top 3 models by AUC
        aucs = [(name, individual_aucs[name]) for name in predictions_dict.keys()]
        aucs.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
        best_3_names = [name for name, _ in aucs[:3]]
        best_3_preds = [predictions_dict[name] for name in best_3_names]
        ensemble_preds = np.mean(best_3_preds, axis=0)
    
    ensemble_auc = roc_auc_score(labels, ensemble_preds)
    return ensemble_preds, ensemble_auc

# Test different ensemble methods
print(f"\nTesting Ensemble Methods:")
print(f"{'Method':<20s} {'AUC':<8s} {'Improvement'}")
print("-" * 40)

ensemble_methods = {
    'simple_average': 'Simple Average',
    'weighted_average': 'Weighted by AUC', 
    'best_3_average': 'Best 3 Models'
}

best_ensemble_auc = 0
best_ensemble_method = None
best_ensemble_preds = None

for method_key, method_name in ensemble_methods.items():
    ens_preds, ens_auc = test_ensemble_method(all_predictions, val_labels, method_key)
    baseline_auc = max(individual_aucs.values())
    improvement = ens_auc - baseline_auc
    
    print(f"{method_name:<20s} {ens_auc:.4f}   +{improvement:.4f}")
    
    if ens_auc > best_ensemble_auc:
        best_ensemble_auc = ens_auc
        best_ensemble_method = method_key
        best_ensemble_preds = ens_preds

print(f"\n Best Ensemble: {ensemble_methods[best_ensemble_method]}")
print(f"Ensemble AUC: {best_ensemble_auc:.4f}")
print(f"Improvement over best individual: +{best_ensemble_auc - max(individual_aucs.values()):.4f}")

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.metrics import recall_score, precision_score, f1_score

# Use your existing variables
y_true_labels = y_true
ensemble_val_preds = ens_preds  # raw probabilities from ensemble

thresholds = np.arange(0.10, 0.76, 0.05)
results = []

for thresh in thresholds:
    y_pred_thresh = (ensemble_val_preds >= thresh).astype(int)
    recall = recall_score(y_true_labels, y_pred_thresh)
    precision = precision_score(y_true_labels, y_pred_thresh)
    f1 = f1_score(y_true_labels, y_pred_thresh)
    
    results.append({
        "Threshold": round(thresh, 2),
        "Recall": recall,
        "Precision": precision,
        "F1": f1
    })

df_thresh = pd.DataFrame(results)
print(df_thresh.to_string(index=False))

# Pick best threshold where recall >= 0.90
df_best = df_thresh[df_thresh["Recall"] >= 0.90].sort_values(by="Precision", ascending=False)
if not df_best.empty:
    best_threshold = df_best.iloc[0]["Threshold"]
    print(f"\nBest threshold for Recall >= 0.90: {best_threshold}")
else:
    print("\nNo threshold meets Recall >= 0.90")

results = []

for thresh in thresholds:
    y_pred_thresh = (ensemble_val_preds >= thresh).astype(int)
    recall = recall_score(y_true_labels, y_pred_thresh)
    precision = precision_score(y_true_labels, y_pred_thresh)
    f1 = f1_score(y_true_labels, y_pred_thresh)
    
    results.append({
        "Threshold": round(thresh, 2),
        "Recall": recall,
        "Precision": precision,
        "F1": f1
    })

df_thresh = pd.DataFrame(results)
print(df_thresh.to_string(index=False))

# Pick best threshold where recall >= 0.90
df_best = df_thresh[df_thresh["Recall"] >= 0.90].sort_values(by="Precision", ascending=False)
if not df_best.empty:
    best_threshold = df_best.iloc[0]["Threshold"]
    best_medical_threshold = best_threshold  # auto-update for deployment
    ensemble_metadata["medical_threshold"] = float(best_threshold)  # persist in metadata
    print(f"\nBest threshold for Recall >= 0.90: {best_threshold}")
    print(f"Updated best_medical_threshold to {best_medical_threshold}")

    # Convert NumPy arrays in ensemble_metadata to lists for JSON saving
    def make_serializable(obj):
        if isinstance(obj, np.ndarray):
            return obj.tolist()
        elif isinstance(obj, dict):
            return {k: make_serializable(v) for k, v in obj.items()}
        elif isinstance(obj, list):
            return [make_serializable(i) for i in obj]
        else:
            return obj

    ensemble_metadata_serializable = make_serializable(ensemble_metadata)

    # Save updated metadata file
    with open("ensemble_metadata.json", "w") as f:
        json.dump(ensemble_metadata_serializable, f, indent=4)
    print("Updated ensemble_metadata.json with new threshold.")
else:
    print("\nNo threshold meets Recall >= 0.90")

#Custom ensemble class

import pickle
import json
import numpy as np
import os
from tensorflow.keras.models import load_model

class BurnClassificationEnsemble:
    """Custom ensemble class for burn classification"""
    
    def __init__(self):
        self.models = {}
        self.model_weights = {}
        self.threshold = 0.35
        self.metadata = {}
        self.input_shape = (224, 224, 1)
    
    def add_model(self, name, model, weight=1.0):
        """Add a model to the ensemble"""
        self.models[name] = model
        self.model_weights[name] = weight
        print(f"Added model '{name}' with weight {weight:.4f}")
    
    def set_threshold(self, threshold):
        """Set the classification threshold"""
        self.threshold = threshold
        print(f"Set classification threshold to {threshold}")
    
    def predict_proba(self, X):
        """Get ensemble probability predictions"""
        if not self.models:
            raise ValueError("No models in ensemble")
        
        if len(X.shape) == 3:
            X = np.expand_dims(X, axis=0)  # Add batch dimension if missing
        
        predictions = []
        total_weight = 0
        
        for name, model in self.models.items():
            try:
                pred = model.predict(X, verbose=0)
                weight = self.model_weights[name]
                predictions.append(pred * weight)
                total_weight += weight
            except Exception as e:
                print(f"Warning: Error predicting with model {name}: {e}")
                continue
        
        if not predictions:
            raise RuntimeError("No models could make predictions")
        
        # Weighted average
        ensemble_pred = np.sum(predictions, axis=0) / total_weight
        return ensemble_pred
    
    def predict(self, X):
        """Get binary predictions using threshold"""
        proba = self.predict_proba(X)
        return (proba >= self.threshold).astype(int)
    
    def evaluate_ensemble(self, X, y_true):
        """Evaluate ensemble performance"""
        from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score, roc_auc_score
        
        proba = self.predict_proba(X)
        predictions = self.predict(X)
        
        metrics = {
            'accuracy': accuracy_score(y_true, predictions),
            'precision': precision_score(y_true, predictions),
            'recall': recall_score(y_true, predictions),
            'f1_score': f1_score(y_true, predictions),
            'auc': roc_auc_score(y_true, proba)
        }
        
        return metrics
    
    def save_ensemble(self, base_path):
        """Save the ensemble models and metadata"""
        # Create directory
        os.makedirs(base_path, exist_ok=True)
        
        # Save individual models
        model_paths = {}
        for name, model in self.models.items():
            model_path = f"{base_path}/{name}_model.h5"
            model.save(model_path)
            model_paths[name] = model_path
            print(f"Saved {name} to {model_path}")
        
        # Save ensemble metadata
        metadata = {
            'model_paths': model_paths,
            'model_weights': self.model_weights,
            'threshold': self.threshold,
            'input_shape': self.input_shape,
            'ensemble_metadata': self.metadata
        }
        
        config_path = f"{base_path}/ensemble_config.json"
        with open(config_path, 'w') as f:
            json.dump(metadata, f, indent=2)
        
        print(f" Ensemble configuration saved to: {config_path}")
        print(f" Complete ensemble saved to: {base_path}")
        return base_path
    
    @classmethod
    def load_ensemble(cls, base_path):
        """Load a saved ensemble"""
        ensemble = cls()
        
        # Load metadata
        config_path = f"{base_path}/ensemble_config.json"
        with open(config_path, 'r') as f:
            config = json.load(f)
        
        print(f"Loading ensemble from: {base_path}")
        
        # Load models
        for name, model_path in config['model_paths'].items():
            try:
                model = load_model(model_path)
                weight = config['model_weights'][name]
                ensemble.add_model(name, model, weight)
                print(f" Loaded {name}")
            except Exception as e:
                print(f" Failed to load {name}: {e}")
        
        ensemble.set_threshold(config['threshold'])
        ensemble.input_shape = tuple(config.get('input_shape', (224, 224, 1)))
        ensemble.metadata = config.get('ensemble_metadata', {})
        
        print(f" Ensemble loaded successfully!")
        return ensemble
    
    def get_model_info(self):
        """Get information about the ensemble"""
        info = {
            'num_models': len(self.models),
            'model_names': list(self.models.keys()),
            'threshold': self.threshold,
            'input_shape': self.input_shape,
            'total_parameters': sum(model.count_params() for model in self.models.values())
        }
        return info

    f1_3rd = report['1']['f1-score']
    
    print(f"{thresh:<10.2f} {accuracy:<10.1%} {recall_3rd:<12.1%} {precision_3rd:<15.1%} {f1_3rd:<8.3f}")
    
    densenet_results[thresh] = {
        'accuracy': accuracy,
        'recall_3rd': recall_3rd,
        'precision_3rd': precision_3rd,
        'f1': f1_3rd
    }

# Compare with ensemble
print(f"\n COMPARISON: DenseNet121 vs Ensemble")
print(f"{'Method':<25} {'Threshold':<10} {'3rd Recall':<12} {'Speed':<15} {'Memory'}")
print("-" * 75)

# Find best DenseNet threshold for high recall
best_densenet_thresh = None
best_densenet_recall = 0
for thresh, results in densenet_results.items():
    if results['recall_3rd'] > best_densenet_recall:
        best_densenet_recall = results['recall_3rd']
        best_densenet_thresh = thresh

print(f"DenseNet121 (optimized)   {best_densenet_thresh:<10.2f} {best_densenet_recall:<12.1%} {'1x (fast)':<15} {'48MB'}")
print(f"Ensemble                  {'0.35':<10} {'96.1%':<12} {'5x (slow)':<15} {'240MB'}")

# Performance difference
recall_diff = 0.961 - best_densenet_recall
print(f"\n Trade-off Analysis:")
print(f"   Ensemble recall advantage: +{recall_diff:.1%}")
print(f"   DenseNet speed advantage:  5x faster")
print(f"   DenseNet memory advantage: 5x less")

# Medical impact assessment
total_3rd_burns = np.sum(all_val_labels)
densenet_missed = int(total_3rd_burns * (1 - best_densenet_recall))
ensemble_missed = int(total_3rd_burns * (1 - 0.961))

print(f"\nMedical Impact (out of {total_3rd_burns} 3rd degree burns):")
print(f"   DenseNet121 would miss: {densenet_missed} cases")
print(f"   Ensemble would miss:    {ensemble_missed} cases")
print(f"   Additional cases caught by ensemble: {densenet_missed - ensemble_missed}")
